<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sleid" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sleid</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Sleided silk,</orth> raw, untwisted silk: <cit><quote>letters . . . with sleided silk enswathed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 48" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>skein of sleid silk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 35</bibl></cit> (Q <emph>sleave silk</emph>). <emph>she weaved the sleided silk,</emph> Per. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 21</bibl>.
